\ headn ( dataset n -- ), head ( dataset -- = 10 headn ): print the first
\ min(n, rows) rows as an aligned table — column names as the header line,
\ two-space gutter, numeric/quantity right-aligned, text left-aligned,
\ :datetime columns rendered by time>iso, other cells by render.

\ === typed TSV dataset: text + numeric columns ===
"name	weight	note
fern	1.5	shade plant
oak	120	tall
moss	0.02	ground cover
ivy	3	climbs walls
" "/tmp/lf143.tsv" write-file
"/tmp/lf143.tsv" read-tsv to plants

plants 2 headn
clear cr

\ n beyond the row count prints every row; head defaults n to 10
plants head
clear cr

\ === quantity and datetime columns ===
{ :when [ 1752000000 1752086400 ] vector 1 s *
  :dose [ 0.5 12 ] vector 1 kg *
  :tag [ "first" "second" ] } 5 headn
clear cr

\ === empty dataset: prints nothing, consumes its arguments ===
{ } 5 headn
99 . cr
